            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> vim.lsp.semantic_tokens happens to have [a debounce mechanism](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/6780e78b0981f52aec9c4ef96356d3fef3742c9a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua#L776-L782), but there doesn't seem to be any way to actually configure it from a user's init.lua.\n> vim.lsp.document_color has no debounce whatsoever and will issue didChange on literally every single letter typed.\n\nYeah, this problem is becoming acute. This is perhaps another case that would be mitigated if we had a common \"debounce\" util. \n\nrelated:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39542\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38999\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/33179#issuecomment-2764583792",
